    <title role="Using the Java Compiler as an Object">Using the Java Compiler as an Object</title>

<para>One form of testing is simply checking whether everything compiles. In particular,
code modifications at one place could introduce compilation errors at another,
unanticipated place. To this end automatic recompilation of entire libraries is
very useful. The following utility program does exactly that.</para>
<para><programlisting>
<xi:include parse="text" href="CompileAll.java"/>
</programlisting></para>
<para><programlisting><![CDATA[
java TestUtils.CompileAll
]]></programlisting></para>
    
